headline: CME Group Announces 2026 Annual Meeting Date
summary: CME Group, the world's leading derivatives marketplace, today announced it will conduct its 2026 annual meeting of shareholders at 10:00 a.m. Central Time on Thursday, May 14, 2026. Additional information will be provided in the company's proxy statement.

headline: CME Outperforms Industry, Trades at a Discount: Time to Hold?
summary: CME Group remains poised for growth, riding on solid global presence, a compelling product portfolio, increased electronic trading and a focus on over-the-counter clearing services.

headline: Has CME Group’s Strong 3 Year Run Left Much Upside From Today’s Price?
summary: Wondering if CME Group is still attractive after its big run, or if most of the easy money has already been made? Here is a closer look at what the current share price might be indicating about its long term value. The stock has cooled slightly in the last month, slipping about 2.0%, but it is still up 17.6% year to date and roughly 20.7% over the last year, on top of an 81.5% gain over 3 years. headline: US Financial 15 Split Corp. Preferred Dividend Declared
summary: TORONTO, Dec. 18, 2025 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- US Financial 15 Split Corp ("US Financial 15") declares its monthly distribution of $0.07075 for each Preferred share, or 10.00% annually based on the previous month end net asset value. Distributions are payable January 9, 2026 to shareholders on record as at December 31, 2025. US Financial 15 invests in a portfolio consisting of 15 U.S. financial services companies as follows: American Express, Bank of America, Bank of New York Mellon Corp., Citigroup
